field.value:
Castle.MonoRail.Framework.Services.AjaxProxyGenerator.PrototypeAjaxProxyGenerator will not generate correct URLs in the JS proxy if the application uses URLs without extensions. The generated prototypes will look like:
edit: function(id, callback)
{
  var r=new Ajax.Request('/TestApp/Items/Edit.', {method: 'get', asynchronous: !!callback, onComplete: callback, parameters: '_=&id='+id+''}); 
if(!callback) return r.transport.responseText;
}
[The URL '/TestApp/Items/Edit.' contains a dot at the end that breaks the link]

The supplied patch fixes the issue.
